   <text><body><seg type="excerpt" xml:id="ex01112025-05-0716-13-58" status="reviewed"><milestone unit="section" n="Cover page (1a)"/>
         <pb edRef="inst:4440" n="1a"/><lb edRef="inst:4440" n="1a1"/> rnaM bshad snying po brgyan ma tshang ba 1 | grub mtha'i rnaM gzhag bris ma 1 | 'jaM dbyangs dpa' gtso'i grub thab ma tshang ba 1 |</seg><seg type="excerpt" xml:id="ex01112025-05-0716-13-582" status="reviewed"><milestone unit="section" n="Incipit (1b1)"/>
         <pb edRef="inst:4440" n="1b"/><lb edRef="inst:4440" n="1b1"/> <lg><l>'jig rten kun dang myi mthun pa'i ||</l>
         <l>zab mo'i don can <rs type="work" ana="corpusmd:unnamed_reference" ref="db:3749">bstan chos 'di</rs> ||</l>
         <l>thugs rjes bdag cag la gsungs pa || </l>
         <l>chos la spyan gyur <rs type="deity">de</rs> la 'dud || </l></lg>
         <note type="translation">I bow to him (i.e., Maitreya) whose eyes are directed towards the Dharma and who, out of compassion, taught to us this treatise of profound meaning (i.e., the Ratnagotravibhāga), which goes against [the conventional wisdom of] the entire world.</note></seg>
         <seg type="excerpt" xml:id="ex001112025-05-2008-21-24" status="reviewed"><rs type="person" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:3747">bcom ldan 'das byams pa</rs>s bde bar gshegs pa'i bka'i dgongs pa phyin ci ma log par gsal <choice><reg>bar</reg><orig>‹ba›r</orig></choice> mdzad pa na | nges pa'i don gi mdo sde rin po che | phyir mi ldog pa'i chos kyi 'khor lo | chos kyi dbyings tshul cig du <lb edRef="inst:4440" n="1b2"/> ston pa | shin tu rnam par dag pa gdon myi za ba'i chos kyi rnam grangs khams thabs cad kyi don rab du ×ston pa | <rs type="work" ana="corpusmd:unnamed_reference" ref="db:3749">theg pa chen po rgyud bla ma'i bstan chos</rs> 'di mdzad pas | theg pa chen po'i don gi de kho na rnam par bzhag pa yin no ||</seg><seg type="excerpt" xml:id="ex1112024-01-23-3" status="reviewed">
            <milestone n="2" unit="section"/>
            <lg><l>dam chos gsung rab nges pa'i don gyi tshul ||</l>
            <l> <rs type="work" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:3749">theg <lb edRef="inst:6267" n="65b1"/> <lb edRef="inst:6265" n="32b2"/> <app><lem wit="inst:4440 inst:6265">chen</lem><rdg wit="inst:4440">chen</rdg><rdg wit="inst:6265">chen</rdg><rdg wit="inst:6272">mchog</rdg><rdg wit="inst:6267">mchog</rdg></app><anchor xml:id="a7"/> <lb edRef="inst:6272" n="69b4"/> bla ma'i bstan <app><lem wit="inst:6272 inst:6267 inst:4440">bcos</lem><rdg wit="inst:6272 inst:6267 inst:4440">bcos</rdg><rdg wit="inst:6265">'chos</rdg></app></rs> 'di bshad <app><lem wit="inst:4440">pas</lem><rdg wit="inst:4440">pas</rdg><rdg wit="inst:6272">la</rdg><rdg wit="inst:6265">la</rdg><rdg wit="inst:6267">las</rdg></app> ||</l> 
            <l>bsod nams thob des sangs rgyas thams cad dang ||</l>
            <l><lb edRef="inst:4440" n="40a3"/> mnyam pa'i chos nyid <rs type="person" ana="corpusmd:unnamed_reference" ref="db:3786">bdag</rs> gis myur thob shog ||||</l></lg>
         <note type="translation">Through the merits that I have attained by explaining the Mahāyānottaratantra (i.e., Ratnagotravibhāga), which contains the system of definitive meaning of the scriptures of the excellent doctrine, may I swiftly attain the true nature (dharmatā) equal to all Buddhas!</note>
         </seg>
         <seg type="excerpt" xml:id="ex1112023-10-18" status="finalized" ana="corpusmd:colophon"><rs type="work" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:4441"><rs type="work" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:3749">theg pa chen po rgyud bla ma'i bstan bcos</rs> kyi don bsdus pa</rs> || <rs type="person" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:3786">smra ba'i seng ge | ngag gi dbang phyug | 'chad gra'i slob dpon | sgra sgyur gyi lo tsa ba chen po | rngog dge slong blo ldan shes rab</rs> kyis mdzad pa <lb edRef="inst:4440" n="40a4"/> rdzogs s+h+yo ||<anchor xml:id="a10"/> he he || ||</seg><seg type="excerpt" xml:id="ex01112025-05-0717-06-56" status="reviewed" ana="corpusmd:colophon"><rs type="work" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:4441">theg pa chen po rgyud bla ma'i bstan <app><lem wit="inst:6272 inst:6267">bcos</lem><rdg wit="inst:6272 inst:6267">bcos</rdg><rdg wit="inst:6265">'chos</rdg></app> kyi don bsdus pa</rs> | <rs type="person" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:3786"><app><lem wit="inst:6272 inst 6267">dge</lem><rdg wit="inst:6272 inst 6267">dge</rdg><rdg wit="inst:6265">rge</rdg></app> slong blo ldan shes rab</rs> kyis sbyar pa'o ||</seg>
      <seg type="excerpt" xml:id="ex01112025-05-0816-03-22" status="reviewed"> <lg><l><lb edRef="inst:6265" n="32b3"/> bla rgyud kyi bstan 'chos 'di la ||</l> <l>brtsams pa <rs type="person" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:3786">blo ldan rngog</rs> gyis brtsams ||</l> <l>bris pa <rs type="person" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:6268">nyang stod ze'u</rs> gyis bris ||</l> <l>yon bdag <rs type="person" ana="corpusmd:named_reference" ref="db:6269">yol ston dar brtsan</rs> lags ||</l></lg></seg></body></text></TEI>
